      "content": "In India, for example, it's essential to avoid eating with your left hand, as it's considered unclean, and to use your right hand when giving or receiving items, such as business cards or gifts. When dining with Indian clients, it's also customary to wait for the host to start eating before you begin, and to avoid finishing a meal completely, as it implies the host didn't provide enough food. In Nigeria, it's customary to greet with a handshake or a kiss on the cheek, and to use formal titles such as \"Chief\" or \"Mr.\" when addressing older men. And of course, it's always best to avoid any physical contact with people from other cultures, as it can be perceived as invasive or disrespectful.",
